  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and involves multiple layers of legislation at national and international levels. Here's an overview:\n\n1. International Level Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation Components:\n- Defining money laundering as a criminal offense\n- Establishing reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Creating mechanisms for asset seizure and recovery\n- Mandating customer due diligence procedures\n- Implementing suspicious transaction reporting systems\n\n3. National Legislation Examples:\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- United Kingdom: Proceeds of Crime Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n\n4. Regulatory Requirements:\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Customer identification protocols\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious activities\n- Regular risk assessments\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
